707219f-a.text:
Village Road North, south side, opposite Lake Street, showing the house occupied by J.S. Van Cleef in 1873? which is still standing in 1929, and to the left of which, partially seen, is No. 28; in the background, is a section of P.S. No. 95.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
707219f-a.folder: Village Rd. N. & Lake St., Brooklyn, NY
707219f-a.original_title: Brooklyn: Village Rd. N. - Lake St.

707094f-a.text:
Ave. U., south side, between Lake and Van Sicklen Streets, showing Village Road North in the background, and P.S. No. 95. This building while it faces Ave. U., has only one number and that is 296 Lake Street.
May 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
707094f-a.folder: Ave. U & Lake St., Brooklyn, NY

707095f-a.text:
Ave. U, south side, west from Lake Street. Also seen is Lake Street, east side, in the foreground, between Village Road north, and Ave. U. At the extreme left, shows a section of Public School No. 95.
April 21, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
